ğŸš¨ Disaster Relief Resource Management System
A comprehensive C-based terminal application for managing disaster relief resource allocation using graph algorithms, priority queues, and hashmaps.

ğŸ“‹ Overview
This system manages the allocation of relief resources across cities after a disaster. Cities are represented as nodes in a weighted graph where roads have distances in kilometers. When a disaster occurs, the system:

Finds the nearest unaffected city with sufficient resources
Allocates and tracks resources via priority queue + hashmap
Calculates the shortest path using Dijkstra's algorithm
Updates city status (Pending, In Transit, Completed)
Displays detailed allocation reports
ğŸ—ï¸ Project Structure
disaster_relief/
â”œâ”€â”€ main.c              # Main program with menu interface
â”œâ”€â”€ graph.c/h           # Weighted adjacency list graph implementation
â”œâ”€â”€ dijkstra.c/h        # Dijkstra's algorithm with min-heap
â”œâ”€â”€ resources.c/h       # Resource allocation with priority queue & hashmap
â”œâ”€â”€ utils.c/h           # Helper functions (input, menu, logging)
â”œâ”€â”€ Makefile            # Build automation
â””â”€â”€ allocation_logs.txt # Auto-generated allocation logs
ğŸ”§ Technical Features
Graph Module (graph.c/h)
Weighted adjacency list representation
Each city stores: ID, name, population, damage level, resources, coordinates
Bidirectional roads with distances in km
Dynamic edge management
Dijkstra Module (dijkstra.c/h)
Min-heap priority queue implementation
O(E log V) time complexity
Shortest path calculation between any two cities
Parent array for path reconstruction
Resources Module (resources.c/h)
Max-heap priority queue for urgent disaster requests
Hashmap for O(1) status tracking
Status states: PENDING â†’ IN_TRANSIT â†’ COMPLETED
Automatic nearest city selection with resource constraints
File-based allocation logging
Utils Module (utils.c/h)
Input validation and sanitization
Cross-platform screen clearing
Menu system with visual formatting
Log file management
ğŸš€ Compilation & Execution
Using Makefile (Recommended)
bash
# Build the project
make

# Build and run
make run

# Clean build artifacts
make clean

# Show help
make help
Manual Compilation
bash
gcc -Wall -Wextra -std=c99 -O2 -o disaster_relief \
    main.c graph.c dijkstra.c resources.c utils.c

./disaster_relief
