ğŸ¯ Menu Options
Display City Network - Shows all cities, connections, and resource levels
Add New City - Dynamically add cities to the network
Add Road Between Cities - Create new connections with distances
Raise Disaster Request - Submit urgent resource requests with priority
Allocate Resources - Process the most urgent request using Dijkstra
Display Allocation Status - View current status of all allocations
View Allocation Logs - Read detailed logs from file
Exit - Clean shutdown with memory deallocation
ğŸ“ Key Algorithms
Dijkstra's Shortest Path
Time Complexity: O(E log V) using min-heap
Space Complexity: O(V)
Finds optimal route for resource transport
Priority Queue (Max-Heap)
Insert: O(log n)
Extract Max: O(log n)
Ensures most urgent requests processed first
HashMap (Chaining)
Insert/Search: O(1) average case
Hash function: (hash * 31 + char) % HASH_SIZE
Tracks allocation status efficiently
ğŸ”’ Safety Features
Input validation on all user inputs
Memory leak prevention with proper cleanup
Bounds checking on array accesses
NULL pointer checks
Include guards in all headers
ğŸ“„ Logging
All allocations are automatically logged to allocation_logs.txt with:

Timestamp
Disaster and support cities
Resources allocated
Distance and route
Formatted for audit trail
ğŸ› ï¸ Requirements
Compiler: GCC (or any C99-compatible compiler)
OS: Linux, macOS, Windows (with GCC/MinGW)
Libraries: Standard C library only (stdio, stdlib, string, limits)
